origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-5"},{"@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-6"},{"@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-7"},{"@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-8"},{"@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-9"},{"@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-10"}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-1","position":1,"name":"What is the difference between a normal cleanser and foaming cleanser?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>\n  The difference between a normal cleanser and a foaming face cleanser comes down to lather. A normal cleanser has a light lather, while a foaming face wash has a more frothy or foaming lather. While both types of \n  <a href=\"https://www.origins.com/products/15342/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers\" target=\"_blank\">cleansers</a> \n  work to help remove dirt, oil, and impurities, it’s really a matter of preference when it comes to wanting a little lather or a lot of lather.\n</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-2","position":2,"name":"Can I use this foaming face wash for double cleansing?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, you can absolutely use our Foaming Face Wash for <a href=\"/stories/skincare-tips/what-is-double-cleansing\">Double Cleansing</a>. We recommend starting your Double Cleanse with an oil-based cleanser first, like our Checks and Balances™ <a href=\"/product/15342/105647/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balancestm-milky-oil/cleanser-makeup-melter\">Milky Oil Cleanser + Makeup Melter</a>, to help dissolve makeup. Then use Checks and Balances™ Frothy Face Wash to wash away any remaining residue and impurities, for skin that’s purified and refreshed.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-3","position":3,"name":"What makes Frothy Face Wash unique?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Our Frothy Face Wash is our #1 best-selling cleanser, and not only that: it’s suitable for all skin types and gentle enough for daily use. It lathers up and rinses away impurities, makeup and excess oils that can lead to blemishes, while leaving dry and oily zones comfortably clean.</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-4","position":4,"name":"Can this cleanser help purify pores and clean an oily T-zone?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Yes. It gently removes excess oil and buildup from areas like the T-zone, leaving skin feeling balanced and refreshed. The formula works to help purify pores of oils that can lead to blemishes and leaves dry and oily zones comfortably clean.</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-5","position":5,"name":"Is this a gentle cleanser that can remove makeup and dirt?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Yes. It effectively lifts away dirt, makeup, and impurities while leaving skin comfortably clean. The frothy lather cleans thoroughly while leaving skin feeling refreshed and clean. It’s gentle enough for everyday use and suitable for skin that prefers a soft, balanced finish.</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-6","position":6,"name":"What does the \r\n  \r\n    Checks and Balances™ Frothy Face Wash\r\n   \r\n  do and how do you use it?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n\t<li>This foaming face cleanser rinses away makeup, impurities and surface oils for skin that feels comfortably clean.</li>\n\t<li>To use: squeeze a pea-size amount into your palm, add warm water to lather, massage onto skin (avoiding eyes), then rinse thoroughly. </li>\n</ul>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-7","position":7,"name":"What is the \r\n  \r\n    Checks and Balances™ Milky Oil Cleanser + Makeup Melter\r\n  \r\n  and how is it used?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n\t<li>This is an oil-to-milk cleanser and makeup remover.</li>\n\t<li>Shake well to activate, apply to dry skin, then add warm water and massage until it turns milky. Rinse clean.</li>\n        <li>It helps dissolve makeup (including long-wear), sunscreen, dirt, and impurities.</li>\n</ul>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-8","position":8,"name":"Are these cleansers suitable for all skin types, including sensitive skin?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>\n  Yes. The \n  <a href=\"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/105647/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balancestm-milky-oil/cleanser-makeup-melter?#/sku/155496\">\n    Checks and Balances™ Milky Oil Cleanser + Makeup Melter\n  </a>\n  is gentle and appropriate for all skin types, including sensitive skin. \n  The \n  <a href=\"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/Checks-and-Balances/Frothy-Face-Wash?#/sku/136917\">\n    Checks and Balances™ Frothy Face Wash\n  </a>\n  is formulated for all skin types as well.\n</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-9","position":9,"name":"Can the \r\n  \r\n    Checks and Balances™ Milky Oil Cleanser + Makeup Melter\r\n  \r\n  remove eye makeup?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Yes. This makeup remover can be used around the eyes to remove eye makeup, including long-wear formulas. It is ophthalmologist-tested.</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash#question-10","position":10,"name":"Can I double cleanse using both products together?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>\n  Yes. Start with the \n  <a href=\"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/105647/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balancestm-milky-oil/cleanser-makeup-melter?#/sku/155496\">\n    Checks and Balances™ Milky Oil Cleanser + Makeup Melter\n  </a>\n  to dissolve makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, then follow with the \n  <a href=\"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/Checks-and-Balances/Frothy-Face-Wash?#/sku/136917\">\n    Checks and Balances™ Frothy Face Wash\n  </a>\n  for a balanced, purified cleanse.\n</p>","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"}]}</script><meta name="google-site-verification" content="MMLrqLwFoCdfc_oNkWh5QkM2LxMcpvZGQPeBPsLexRI"><meta name="google-site-verification" content="UOVCmqXc6eWVSFCZLpBp4NTd6X-2Rw4kZf7hQT6OCvI"><meta name="msvalidate.01" content="F70C8C52EB5EA67002C696334C064EF5"><link rel="shortcut icon" href="https://www.origins.com/media/images/favicon.ico"><link rel="preconnect" href="https://ncsa.sdapi.io/" crossorigin=""><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org/","@type":"ProductGroup","name":"Checks and Balances&#8482;","image":"https://www.origins.com/media/export/cms/products/1000x1000/origins_sku_048E01_1000x1000_0.jpg","description":"A little goes a long way: Squeeze a pea-size amount into the palm of your hand and add warm. Massage onto skin to work cleanser into a lather, avoiding eyes. Rinse thoroughly. Look and feel comfortably clean.Pro Tip:Gently cleanse with our #1 Frothy Face Wash to dissolve impurities and makeup, then finish with our Checks & Balances Polishing Face Scrub  to gently exfoliate and smooth.When to Use:-During your morning ritual-In the shower to self-care-After a long day in makeup &nbsp;","url":"https://www.origins.com/product/15342/11226/skincare/cleanse/face-wash-and-cleansers/checks-and-balances/frothy-face-wash","brand":{"@type":"Brand","name":"Origins","image":"https://www.origins.com/media/images/global/OR_LOGO_Secondary_BLACK.png","url":"https://www.origins.com/"},"sku":"048E01","productGroupID":11226,"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.5,"reviewCount":4682},"variesBy":"https://schema.org/size","hasVariant":[{"@type":"Product","sku":"048E01","image":"https://www.origins.com/media/export/cms/products/600x600_gray/origins_sku_048E01_600x600_gray_0.jpg","name":"Checks and Balances&#8482; - 5.0 fl. oz.","description":"A little goes a long way: Squeeze a pea-size amount into the palm of yo